{"id":"auth_canary-dkl","title":"Provision auth-canary runtime secrets and validate deployment","description":"Before auth-canary can run on pi, three actions are required:\n\n1. Create agenix secret:\n   cd /home/urist/machines_conf\n   agenix -e secrets/pi/auth-canary-env.age\n   Content:\n     ZITADEL_ADMIN_TOKEN=<service account token>\n     BAO_ADMIN_TOKEN=<openbao token>\n     ZITADEL_CA_CERT_PATH=/path/to/zitadel-ca.pem\n     BAO_CA_CERT_PATH=/path/to/bao-ca.pem\n     BAO_ZITADEL_ISSUER=https://homeserver:8443\n\n2. Validate nix flake check + dry-run build (requires SSH keys for private fleet repos):\n   cd /home/urist/machines_conf\n   nix flake check\n   nix build .#nixosConfigurations.pi.config.system.build.toplevel --dry-run\n\n3. Deploy to pi and verify auth-canary.service starts:\n   systemctl status auth-canary\n   journalctl -u auth-canary -f","status":"in_progress","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-05-01T06:11:24.385119797Z","created_by":"urist","updated_at":"2026-05-01T06:25:01.852914538Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
